      void buildCloseButton​(java.lang.String text)
      Build a button for the close action.

      If the parameter was null this will use the text set up in @TPresenter{decorator= @TDecorator{closeButtonText=''}} but if the given TModelView was not annotated with TPresenter or with a custom view annotation which contains a TPresenter a default string (TAnnotationDefaultValue.TVIEW_closeButtonText) will be used.

      This will initialize with "t-button" id.

        public void buildCloseButton​(java.lang.String text)

        Build a button for the close action.

        If the parameter was null this will use the text set up in @TPresenter{decorator= @TDecorator{closeButtonText=''}} but if the given TModelView was not annotated with TPresenter or with a custom view annotation which contains a TPresenter a default string (TAnnotationDefaultValue.TVIEW_closeButtonText) will be used.

        This will initialize with "t-button" id.
